Let $h$ be the length of the altitude from $A$ in $\triangle ABC$. Then \[
2007=\frac{1}{2}\cdot BC\cdot h=\frac{1}{2}\cdot 223\cdot h,
\]so $h=18$.  Thus $A$ is on one of the lines $y=18$ or $y=-18$.

